1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:02,877
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

2
00:00:02,961 --> 00:00:06,506
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,591 --> 00:00:10,677
- <i>♪ Fix this</i> ♪
- <i>♪ Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,760 --> 00:00:12,887
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,971 --> 00:00:16,766
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i>
<i>In the tangle</i> ♪

6
00:00:17,392 --> 00:00:20,061
[Audrey] <i>I hope I can finally</i>
<i>be with my daughter.</i>

7
00:00:20,145 --> 00:00:22,689
[Gavin] <i>The DNA test results</i>
<i>are coming out today.</i>

8
00:00:22,772 --> 00:00:25,233
- [in English] Ah, what’s the result?
- [in English] It’s a match, Dad.

9
00:00:25,316 --> 00:00:26,901
[Audrey] <i>She really</i>
<i>is my missing daughter.</i>

10
00:00:26,985 --> 00:00:27,819
[in English] <i>I want to see her.</i>

11
00:00:27,902 --> 00:00:29,779
[in English] <i>Hello, Janine.</i>

12
00:00:29,863 --> 00:00:31,865
[Janine] <i>I don’t understand.</i>

13
00:00:31,948 --> 00:00:33,825
[Roma] <i>It’s simple, Janine.</i>

14
00:00:33,908 --> 00:00:36,536
<i>Ma’am Audrey is your real mother.</i>

15
00:00:36,619 --> 00:00:38,872
[Janine] This will be my home? Really?

16
00:00:38,955 --> 00:00:42,208
You were about to leave the country
when your child was kidnapped?

17
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:43,376
[Rita] <i>By my ex-husband.</i>

18
00:00:43,460 --> 00:00:45,295
[Atoy] <i>I’ve located the father</i>
<i>and his daughter.</i>

19
00:00:45,378 --> 00:00:47,547
[Mercado] <i>This mission is delicate,</i>

20
00:00:47,630 --> 00:00:49,215
<i>because a child is involved.</i>

21
00:00:49,799 --> 00:00:51,760
[Ibyang] <i>I’m upset with Master!</i>

22
00:00:51,843 --> 00:00:55,096
He said he won’t come with me
to the field trip tomorrow!

23
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:58,224
[Janine] <i>Oh, we actually have a field trip</i>
<i>tomorrow! Let’s go there instead.</i>

24
00:00:58,308 --> 00:00:59,934
[Red] Your plan was genius.

25
00:01:00,018 --> 00:01:01,936
I love it when your sister
looks like a fool.

26
00:01:02,020 --> 00:01:04,522
[Martina] <i>That’s my revenge on her</i>
<i>for being such a bitch in our lives.</i>

27
00:01:04,606 --> 00:01:07,484
[Audrey] Wait. Have you seen my phone?
Weren’t you holding it earlier?

28
00:01:07,567 --> 00:01:10,278
‪PREVIOUSLY

29
00:01:10,862 --> 00:01:11,946
[in English] Ah, I found it.

30
00:01:14,908 --> 00:01:15,909
[music fades]

31
00:01:15,992 --> 00:01:18,203
[pleasant music playing]

32
00:01:38,515 --> 00:01:40,892
[chuckles]

33
00:01:40,975 --> 00:01:43,061
[pensive music playing]

34
00:01:43,144 --> 00:01:44,354
Here!

35
00:01:44,437 --> 00:01:46,981
Happy birthday, my child!

36
00:01:47,482 --> 00:01:50,777
Sorry, this is all Papa could give.

37
00:01:52,362 --> 00:01:53,446
Here.

38
00:01:57,617 --> 00:01:58,785
Make a wish first.

39
00:02:01,496 --> 00:02:03,248
This is my wish, Papa.

40
00:02:03,331 --> 00:02:05,416
For us to go to the theme park.

41
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:06,793
[chuckles softly]

42
00:02:06,876 --> 00:02:08,586
Are you sure?

43
00:02:08,670 --> 00:02:11,214
You know, on your birthday,
wishes are unlimited.

44
00:02:11,798 --> 00:02:14,592
My only wish, Papa,

45
00:02:14,676 --> 00:02:16,845
is to be with you forever.

46
00:02:16,928 --> 00:02:19,139
I hope we never get separated.

47
00:02:19,222 --> 00:02:20,557
Come here.

48
00:02:20,640 --> 00:02:22,559
[lively chattering]

49
00:02:23,143 --> 00:02:25,478
That will never happen.

50
00:02:25,562 --> 00:02:26,896
That’s Papa’s promise.

51
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:29,983
[mysterious music playing]

52
00:02:32,026 --> 00:02:33,862
[chuckles]

53
00:02:35,405 --> 00:02:36,281
[both] Wah!

54
00:02:36,364 --> 00:02:37,657
[laughs]

55
00:02:37,740 --> 00:02:38,575
Let’s eat.

56
00:02:41,244 --> 00:02:42,787
[line rings]

57
00:02:43,538 --> 00:02:44,372
Hello, sir?

58
00:02:44,455 --> 00:02:45,707
Any update?

59
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:47,375
I’m here at the theme park.

60
00:02:48,334 --> 00:02:50,420
[suspicious music playing]

61
00:02:52,171 --> 00:02:54,757
It looks like a birthday celebration
for the child.

62
00:02:56,342 --> 00:02:58,803
Anyway, there are lots of people here.
It’ll be easy to intercept them.

63
00:03:02,724 --> 00:03:04,017
You can call the mother.

64
00:03:07,145 --> 00:03:09,772
Tell her in about 30 minutes,

65
00:03:11,274 --> 00:03:13,026
I can hand her over the child to her.

66
00:03:13,985 --> 00:03:15,194
[in English] Good.

67
00:03:16,362 --> 00:03:17,405
Okay, sir.

68
00:03:21,326 --> 00:03:23,328
[music fades]

69
00:03:23,411 --> 00:03:25,788
- [dramatic sting]
- [tense music playing]

70
00:03:34,172 --> 00:03:36,966
[suave theme music playing]

71
00:03:39,302 --> 00:03:41,137
[motorcycle revving]

72
00:03:41,221 --> 00:03:42,096
[sewing machine whirring]

73
00:03:42,180 --> 00:03:43,056
[scratches]

74
00:03:43,139 --> 00:03:44,015
[snipping]

75
00:03:45,683 --> 00:03:48,937
[sewing machine whirring]

76
00:03:49,020 --> 00:03:51,147
- [gun cocks]
- [gunshots blasting]

77
00:03:51,231 --> 00:03:52,315
[gunshots blasting]

78
00:03:54,692 --> 00:03:57,153
[snipping]

79
00:03:57,237 --> 00:03:58,988
[electronic blipping]

80
00:04:03,159 --> 00:04:04,535
[music fades]

81
00:04:04,619 --> 00:04:06,412
Here I go! Oh!

82
00:04:06,496 --> 00:04:08,873
I’ll do it, I’ll do it! Let me do it!

83
00:04:08,957 --> 00:04:10,416
So, the kid can finally win something.

84
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:12,669
[Emerson] The three of you keep losing.

85
00:04:12,752 --> 00:04:14,963
As if you’re any better!

86
00:04:15,046 --> 00:04:17,131
Even Karla, who plays basketball,
can’t even score.

87
00:04:17,215 --> 00:04:20,051
- Hey! I did win!
- [quirky music playing]

88
00:04:20,134 --> 00:04:22,804
But the prize was just juice.

89
00:04:22,887 --> 00:04:24,597
There, Ibyang is drinking it already!

90
00:04:25,306 --> 00:04:26,432
[Tonet] Wait! Oh!

91
00:04:26,516 --> 00:04:29,435
[in Visayan] Give Emerson a chance!
He’s got this!

92
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:30,603
- Brother, good luck!
- We’ll give it to you! All right.

93
00:04:30,687 --> 00:04:32,272
Focus, Brother, focus!
Another one like that!

94
00:04:32,355 --> 00:04:33,606
- [Karla] Shoot it!
- [Tonet] Oh, there.

95
00:04:33,690 --> 00:04:34,857
Oh, oh, oh. Yes, go.

96
00:04:34,941 --> 00:04:36,067
- One more, bro. More.
- I’m nervous.

97
00:04:36,150 --> 00:04:37,694
- Yes. More, more, more!
- Nervous?

98
00:04:37,777 --> 00:04:38,778
[both exclaims]

99
00:04:38,861 --> 00:04:40,029
- He’s good!
- See? I told you!

100
00:04:40,113 --> 00:04:42,115
- Tell him, "Go, baby!"
- There! Oh, oh!

101
00:04:42,198 --> 00:04:43,741
- One more, bro. One more.
- Oh, one more.

102
00:04:43,825 --> 00:04:45,535
Ibyang… This is for you, Ibyang.

103
00:04:45,618 --> 00:04:46,536
Oh, nothing.

104
00:04:46,619 --> 00:04:48,037
- Oh! Nothing again.
- Just like earlier.

105
00:04:48,121 --> 00:04:49,789
- Oh, no!
- It was just luck earlier.

106
00:04:49,872 --> 00:04:51,374
Yeah, just luck.

107
00:04:51,457 --> 00:04:53,042
- It’s over!
- Nothing! it’s over.

108
00:04:53,626 --> 00:04:56,087
[music concludes]

109
00:04:59,257 --> 00:05:00,883
Are we going in there, Papa?

110
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:03,678
Yes, we are dear!
Are you excited? Let’s go!

111
00:05:03,761 --> 00:05:05,346
[chuckles]

112
00:05:05,430 --> 00:05:06,806
[lively chattering]

113
00:05:06,889 --> 00:05:08,433
[Noel] Hold on to me, okay?

114
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:14,731
[suave theme music playing]

115
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:36,210
[music fades]

116
00:05:37,462 --> 00:05:40,339
[in English] Look, Janine,
the flowers are so cute!

117
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:42,133
So, Janine? Are you enjoying?

118
00:05:42,717 --> 00:05:43,676
It’s fine.

119
00:05:44,552 --> 00:05:45,720
I’m getting hungry.

120
00:05:47,096 --> 00:05:49,807
All right, I’ll… I’ll buy food, dear.

121
00:05:50,475 --> 00:05:52,685
- Watch over her, Gavin.
- Sure, Auntie.

122
00:05:54,145 --> 00:05:56,439
[pensive music playing]

123
00:05:57,482 --> 00:05:59,442
So, Janine, what do you want to ride next?

124
00:06:00,318 --> 00:06:02,612
- They’re all cool!
- I’m really hungry.

125
00:06:02,695 --> 00:06:04,822
[phone ringing]

126
00:06:10,536 --> 00:06:12,747
Stay here, okay?
Wait, I’ll just answer this quickly.

127
00:06:12,830 --> 00:06:14,040
[phone ringing]

128
00:06:14,123 --> 00:06:15,333
[in English] Bro, what’s up?

129
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:19,212
Yeah, I’m here at the theme park.

130
00:06:19,295 --> 00:06:20,296
Are you coming?

131
00:06:21,798 --> 00:06:24,467
[somber music playing]

132
00:06:26,094 --> 00:06:27,178
Janine!

133
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:28,471
‪[exhales]

134
00:06:28,554 --> 00:06:29,806
You came too?

135
00:06:29,889 --> 00:06:33,142
So, your mom allowed you?

136
00:06:33,726 --> 00:06:35,394
Why are you acting close to me?

137
00:06:37,021 --> 00:06:38,815
What did you tell me the other day?

138
00:06:39,482 --> 00:06:42,610
That we’re both without parents?

139
00:06:42,693 --> 00:06:45,696
That’s why I’m happy to see you here.

140
00:06:46,989 --> 00:06:48,783
So, you think we’re in the same situation?

141
00:06:50,451 --> 00:06:52,662
You’re alone now, Ibyang.

142
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:54,288
Why?

143
00:06:55,081 --> 00:06:57,500
Because I already found my real mommy.

144
00:06:58,334 --> 00:07:00,711
She looked for me, Ibyang!

145
00:07:01,504 --> 00:07:02,964
- [dramatic sting]
- Really?

146
00:07:03,548 --> 00:07:04,841
[snickers]

147
00:07:05,633 --> 00:07:07,593
Awww.

148
00:07:09,011 --> 00:07:11,639
Ibyang is still adopted.

149
00:07:11,722 --> 00:07:13,683
[dramatic sting]

150
00:07:13,766 --> 00:07:15,518
[cackles]

151
00:07:16,102 --> 00:07:19,480
But me, I found my real mommy.

152
00:07:20,731 --> 00:07:23,860
She’s beautiful like me, and she
even bought me a lovely dress.

153
00:07:24,819 --> 00:07:25,736
You?

154
00:07:26,904 --> 00:07:28,072
Where’s…

155
00:07:28,156 --> 00:07:29,866
Where’s your fake dad?

156
00:07:30,825 --> 00:07:32,743
What did he buy for you?

157
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:44,630
This rag?

158
00:07:45,548 --> 00:07:46,549
This?

159
00:07:48,259 --> 00:07:50,803
You know, if your mom
were really looking for you,

160
00:07:50,887 --> 00:07:53,264
maybe you’d be wearing something nicer,

161
00:07:53,848 --> 00:07:55,099
like me.

162
00:07:56,058 --> 00:07:59,145
But how would she look for you

163
00:07:59,228 --> 00:08:01,397
if she doesn’t love you?

164
00:08:02,315 --> 00:08:05,026
[cackling]

165
00:08:06,235 --> 00:08:08,988
You look uglier when you cry.

166
00:08:09,489 --> 00:08:10,865
Move aside!

167
00:08:11,949 --> 00:08:14,952
[music intensifies]

168
00:08:24,170 --> 00:08:26,464
- [woman] <i>Oh, no. What now?</i>
- [music fades]

169
00:08:26,547 --> 00:08:28,799
Where was she rushed to?

170
00:08:28,883 --> 00:08:30,927
Will Papa be able to go?

171
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:33,179
Who’s with her at the hospital?

172
00:08:36,265 --> 00:08:37,892
All right, all right.

173
00:08:37,975 --> 00:08:39,560
I’ll find a way.

174
00:08:39,644 --> 00:08:43,439
But if I leave here, I won’t get paid.

175
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:45,566
I need money for the hospital.

176
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:49,570
[suspicious music playing]

177
00:08:49,654 --> 00:08:51,531
Uh, miss…

178
00:08:55,326 --> 00:08:57,119
I overheard your conversation.

179
00:08:57,203 --> 00:08:58,788
I’m the new trainee here.

180
00:08:59,372 --> 00:09:02,208
Yes, I just started.

181
00:09:02,291 --> 00:09:05,044
Do you want me to cover for you?

182
00:09:05,127 --> 00:09:06,587
I’ll stand in for you.

183
00:09:06,671 --> 00:09:09,840
Thanks, but I need my pay here too.

184
00:09:10,716 --> 00:09:12,093
We’re paid daily.

185
00:09:12,176 --> 00:09:15,930
No, no, no. The full salary
will still go to you.

186
00:09:16,013 --> 00:09:17,431
I’ll just do the work.

187
00:09:17,515 --> 00:09:18,975
They won’t even know.

188
00:09:19,642 --> 00:09:21,352
We wear costumes anyway.

189
00:09:21,936 --> 00:09:23,354
I’ll handle it. I’ll cover you.

190
00:09:23,437 --> 00:09:25,606
- Really?
- Yes! I’m not doing anything,

191
00:09:25,690 --> 00:09:27,066
and I’m a trainee here.

192
00:09:27,149 --> 00:09:28,693
I want to learn how to scare, right?

193
00:09:28,776 --> 00:09:30,528
Whoa! [chuckles]

194
00:09:30,611 --> 00:09:32,446
Come on! I’ll cover for you.

195
00:09:33,114 --> 00:09:35,157
[soft rock music playing]

196
00:09:35,241 --> 00:09:36,951
- [woman] Thank you.
- [Atoy] Alright.

197
00:09:42,707 --> 00:09:44,834
[lively chattering]

198
00:09:44,917 --> 00:09:46,877
You dirtied my dress!

199
00:09:46,961 --> 00:09:49,130
Wait, wait! What happened here?

200
00:09:49,213 --> 00:09:50,673
[panting]

201
00:09:50,756 --> 00:09:53,175
She spilled juice
on the dress Mommy gave me.

202
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:55,303
She’s jealous!

203
00:09:56,345 --> 00:09:58,431
I didn’t mean it!

204
00:09:59,557 --> 00:10:02,643
You pushed me,
that’s why the juice spilled!

205
00:10:02,727 --> 00:10:04,270
- Liar!
- Stop it, stop it!

206
00:10:04,353 --> 00:10:07,023
Get away from here! I’ll handle this.

207
00:10:07,607 --> 00:10:10,484
[somber music playing]

208
00:10:11,569 --> 00:10:12,903
No.

209
00:10:12,987 --> 00:10:15,114
I’m telling Mommy.

210
00:10:16,032 --> 00:10:18,326
What do you want? Food?
Let’s buy you something to eat.

211
00:10:18,409 --> 00:10:19,243
No!

212
00:10:19,327 --> 00:10:22,413
I’ll wait for Mommy. I’m telling Mommy!

213
00:10:22,496 --> 00:10:26,125
[rousing music playing]

214
00:10:27,543 --> 00:10:30,254
[screaming and squealing]

215
00:10:32,256 --> 00:10:35,051
[frantic music playing]

216
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:48,773
[Sabina] Papa, don’t let go of me, okay?

217
00:10:48,856 --> 00:10:50,316
[Noel] Of course, my child.

218
00:10:50,399 --> 00:10:53,235
Actually, we’ll change exits.

219
00:10:53,819 --> 00:10:56,072
[Sabina] We’re not going to finish this?

220
00:10:56,155 --> 00:10:57,573
[Noel] The truth is, dear…

221
00:10:58,699 --> 00:11:01,077
I feel like a man
was following us earlier.

222
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:02,662
Looks like your mommy sent him.

223
00:11:04,121 --> 00:11:05,081
Come on.

224
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:08,584
- [growls]
- [Sabina screams]

225
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:12,338
- [frantic music continues]
- [screaming and squealing]

226
00:11:16,842 --> 00:11:19,845
- [music swells]
- [screaming and squealing]

227
00:11:33,234 --> 00:11:36,362
[ominous music playing]

228
00:11:40,950 --> 00:11:43,327
Just don’t fall, child.

229
00:11:44,161 --> 00:11:45,454
- [growls]
- [Sabina screams]

230
00:11:45,538 --> 00:11:47,373
Hey! You’re not allowed to touch here!

231
00:11:47,456 --> 00:11:49,083
- [grunts]
- [Noel] Sabina!

232
00:11:49,166 --> 00:11:52,002
- [Sabina] Papa!
- [Noel] Sabina!

233
00:11:52,586 --> 00:11:55,798
[Sabina] Let go of me! Let go of me!

234
00:11:55,881 --> 00:11:57,675
Let go of me!

235
00:11:57,758 --> 00:12:01,470
Let go of me! Let go of me!

236
00:12:02,054 --> 00:12:04,306
- [grunts]
- [tense music playing]

237
00:12:07,726 --> 00:12:09,145
Sabina!

238
00:12:10,438 --> 00:12:12,231
[Sabina] Let go of me!

239
00:12:12,314 --> 00:12:13,149
[Noel shouts]

240
00:12:15,276 --> 00:12:16,902
Let go of me!

241
00:12:16,986 --> 00:12:18,320
[Noel] My child?

242
00:12:23,534 --> 00:12:25,703
Why weren’t you looking after her?
I was playing this game!

243
00:12:25,786 --> 00:12:27,621
- [Emerson] I couldn’t see.
- You were beside each other…

244
00:12:27,705 --> 00:12:30,040
- We’re dead if Brother Atoy finds out.
- She was next to you. You didn’t notice?

245
00:12:30,124 --> 00:12:31,792
Atoy will kill me.

246
00:12:31,876 --> 00:12:33,002
- [Emerson] There she is, there she is!
- [Karla] Here comes Ibyang!

247
00:12:33,085 --> 00:12:34,253
[all] Hey, Ibyang!

248
00:12:34,336 --> 00:12:35,421
- Hey!
- Come here!

249
00:12:35,504 --> 00:12:37,590
Where have you been?

250
00:12:37,673 --> 00:12:39,258
Uh, wha-what happened?

251
00:12:39,341 --> 00:12:40,885
Why? What happened to you?

252
00:12:40,968 --> 00:12:42,845
[somber music playing]

253
00:12:42,928 --> 00:12:46,682
Ibyang, if you don’t speak,
we won’t know how to help you.

254
00:12:51,479 --> 00:12:52,730
I’m okay.

255
00:12:53,564 --> 00:12:55,524
Don’t worry about me.

256
00:13:00,237 --> 00:13:02,114
Uh… Uh--

257
00:13:02,198 --> 00:13:05,242
Do you want to play something else?
Let’s play something else.

258
00:13:05,326 --> 00:13:06,410
- [Tonet] Yes, let’s go!
- [Ame] There are more rides!

259
00:13:06,494 --> 00:13:07,661
[Ame] Where do you want to go?

260
00:13:07,745 --> 00:13:10,122
- Yes, rides! That’s it.
- Rides?

261
00:13:10,206 --> 00:13:12,291
- Rides will make her scream.
- Yes, that works. Alright!

262
00:13:12,875 --> 00:13:14,710
So, where? Where do you want to go?

263
00:13:16,212 --> 00:13:21,383
- [Sabina] No! Let me go! Let go of me!
- [tense music playing]

264
00:13:21,467 --> 00:13:23,719
Let me go!

265
00:13:23,802 --> 00:13:26,889
I don’t want you! I don’t want you!

266
00:13:30,768 --> 00:13:31,852
Let go of me!

267
00:13:31,936 --> 00:13:33,646
- I won’t hurt you!
- [Sabina wails] I don’t want you!

268
00:13:33,729 --> 00:13:35,439
Don’t worry. I’ll take you back
to your mother!

269
00:13:35,523 --> 00:13:37,816
- [Sabina] I don’t want you!
- I won’t hurt you.

270
00:13:37,900 --> 00:13:40,069
- Don't worry--
- I’ll kill you before you can do that!

271
00:13:40,152 --> 00:13:42,655
[intense music playing]

272
00:13:44,615 --> 00:13:46,784
Sabina, child, don’t worry.

273
00:13:46,867 --> 00:13:49,036
I will protect you.
That person won’t hurt you.

274
00:13:49,119 --> 00:13:50,955
I have no intention of hurting your child.

275
00:13:51,539 --> 00:13:54,416
Fine, if you hurt me, if you choose that,

276
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:56,293
your child might be traumatized.

277
00:13:56,377 --> 00:13:58,921
Isn’t my child already traumatized
by what you’re doing?

278
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:00,839
- [grunting]
- [energetic music playing]

279
00:14:00,923 --> 00:14:02,758
[grunts]

280
00:14:06,971 --> 00:14:08,722
That’s nothing!

281
00:14:09,306 --> 00:14:10,391
I know kung fu!

282
00:14:11,517 --> 00:14:12,977
[tense music playing]

283
00:14:13,060 --> 00:14:14,186
Really now.

284
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:16,397
Give me my child!

285
00:14:16,855 --> 00:14:17,898
[music swells]

286
00:14:18,524 --> 00:14:19,692
[growls]

287
00:14:20,192 --> 00:14:21,485
[music fades]

288
00:14:22,361 --> 00:14:23,612
Please, have mercy.

289
00:14:24,989 --> 00:14:26,031
[sobs]

290
00:14:26,115 --> 00:14:29,743
Give me my child.
I don’t really know kung fu.

291
00:14:30,536 --> 00:14:32,246
[sobs]

292
00:14:32,329 --> 00:14:34,373
I’m just an ordinary person.

293
00:14:34,456 --> 00:14:35,499
[sobs]

294
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:38,377
I just want to be with my child.

295
00:14:39,211 --> 00:14:40,796
Is that wrong?

296
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:42,840
‪[somber music playing]

297
00:14:42,923 --> 00:14:44,592
[sobbing]

298
00:14:44,675 --> 00:14:47,970
My wife left me for another man,
because she wanted to--

299
00:14:50,222 --> 00:14:52,308
She wanted someone richer.

300
00:14:53,851 --> 00:14:56,103
And now, she’s taking my child!

301
00:14:56,186 --> 00:14:58,188
[sobbing]

302
00:15:00,858 --> 00:15:02,943
I raised Sabina.

303
00:15:05,070 --> 00:15:07,948
When she’s sick, I take care of her.

304
00:15:09,325 --> 00:15:11,452
I became her mother and father

305
00:15:11,535 --> 00:15:14,955
while her mother was busy with work.

306
00:15:15,664 --> 00:15:17,374
Busy with her man!

307
00:15:21,045 --> 00:15:22,963
[sobbing]

308
00:15:26,258 --> 00:15:29,345
I made a promise to Sabina
that we won’t ever be separated.

309
00:15:32,598 --> 00:15:35,684
That’s my only wish on my birthday. [sobs]

310
00:15:35,768 --> 00:15:38,687
To be with Daddy forever!

311
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:39,980
[sobbing]

312
00:15:40,064 --> 00:15:41,857
[Noel] Please, have mercy.

313
00:15:43,484 --> 00:15:46,403
I don’t want to break my promise to her.

314
00:15:48,030 --> 00:15:49,782
She’s the only one I have!

315
00:15:49,865 --> 00:15:52,034
[melancholic music playing]

316
00:15:52,117 --> 00:15:54,912
[sobbing]

317
00:16:03,921 --> 00:16:05,714
Your ex-wife is coming here.

318
00:16:08,342 --> 00:16:10,427
She asked me to take her.

319
00:16:11,428 --> 00:16:12,763
So if I were you…

320
00:16:13,847 --> 00:16:15,224
talk to her,

321
00:16:16,809 --> 00:16:18,852
because if you continue with your plan

322
00:16:18,936 --> 00:16:20,479
to run away with her…

323
00:16:21,438 --> 00:16:23,732
you’ll never see your child.

324
00:16:23,816 --> 00:16:25,859
Because you’ll end up in jail.

325
00:16:28,362 --> 00:16:30,030
If I were you, talk to your wife.

326
00:16:34,410 --> 00:16:36,078
[Noel sobs]

327
00:16:38,539 --> 00:16:41,375
How’s everything? Can we get my child now?

328
00:16:42,501 --> 00:16:43,711
[Mercado, in English] Yes.

329
00:16:43,794 --> 00:16:47,131
[in English] My man will be here
with the kid anytime now.

330
00:16:52,469 --> 00:16:53,637
Follow me.

331
00:16:54,555 --> 00:16:57,224
It’s good we found your child
before our flight tomorrow.

332
00:16:57,808 --> 00:17:00,561
Perfect, she can enter boarding school.

333
00:17:01,061 --> 00:17:03,480
[Rita] Is that still your plan, Maxwell?

334
00:17:03,564 --> 00:17:08,235
Can't we just enroll Sabina
where we’ll live in Switzerland?

335
00:17:08,318 --> 00:17:12,031
I don’t want to be far from her.
She’s still too young!

336
00:17:12,114 --> 00:17:15,701
[Maxwell] How can we build our family
if your child is here?

337
00:17:16,201 --> 00:17:18,495
You’ll devote all your time to her.

338
00:17:18,579 --> 00:17:21,790
If it were up to me,
I would’ve left her with your ex.

339
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:24,251
But you insisted, didn’t you?

340
00:17:24,334 --> 00:17:26,211
[in English] Well, this
is my compromise, Rita.

341
00:17:27,171 --> 00:17:30,049
[in English] Either boarding school
or we leave her here.

342
00:17:30,132 --> 00:17:32,509
[tense sting]

343
00:17:33,677 --> 00:17:35,888
I don’t want to go to boarding school.

344
00:17:35,971 --> 00:17:38,640
[sobs] And where will they take me?

345
00:17:38,724 --> 00:17:40,726
I don’t know anyone there.

346
00:17:40,809 --> 00:17:43,270
[music swells]

347
00:17:43,353 --> 00:17:44,980
- [Noel] Hmm.
- Let’s go.

348
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:47,524
[tense music playing]

349
00:17:51,445 --> 00:17:53,822
That’s Sabina’s voice!
That’s my child’s voice!

350
00:17:56,784 --> 00:17:57,659
[Maxwell] Well, where’s your man?

351
00:17:57,743 --> 00:17:59,453
[in English] Where’s that damn kid?

352
00:17:59,536 --> 00:18:00,871
[music fades]

353
00:18:00,954 --> 00:18:02,498
What? How did that happen?

354
00:18:02,581 --> 00:18:04,833
I thought your tracker was good?

355
00:18:05,501 --> 00:18:08,670
The father noticed
they were being followed.

356
00:18:08,754 --> 00:18:11,715
He went into the horror house, but…

357
00:18:11,799 --> 00:18:13,592
wasn’t seen coming out.

358
00:18:14,176 --> 00:18:15,385
Maybe…

359
00:18:16,053 --> 00:18:17,930
he escaped through another exit.

360
00:18:18,806 --> 00:18:21,642
They tried to trace them, but…

361
00:18:22,309 --> 00:18:23,310
nothing.

362
00:18:23,977 --> 00:18:25,312
Looks like they have disappeared.

363
00:18:25,395 --> 00:18:28,565
But they can still be found, right, sir?

364
00:18:28,649 --> 00:18:30,234
Ah, yes. It’s possible!

365
00:18:30,317 --> 00:18:34,696
But it will be harder now, because
they know someone is tailing them.

366
00:18:36,990 --> 00:18:38,242
[in English] Give us more time.

367
00:18:38,826 --> 00:18:42,996
Maybe a few more days or a week. Depends.

368
00:18:43,080 --> 00:18:45,707
[in English] Well, sorry!
We don’t have the luxury of time.

369
00:18:45,791 --> 00:18:47,417
Our flight is tomorrow.

370
00:18:48,544 --> 00:18:50,129
Your tracker was useless.

371
00:18:50,212 --> 00:18:53,423
[in English] Let’s go, Rita.
We’ve wasted more than enough.

372
00:18:54,174 --> 00:18:55,134
[in English] Let’s go!

373
00:18:56,051 --> 00:18:58,470
[pensive music playing]

374
00:19:01,932 --> 00:19:03,100
[car engine starts]

375
00:19:13,485 --> 00:19:16,446
[stammers] What happened, dear?

376
00:19:16,530 --> 00:19:17,531
Gavin?

377
00:19:18,323 --> 00:19:20,325
One of my schoolmates…

378
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:23,912
dirtied the clothes you gave me, Mommy.

379
00:19:24,496 --> 00:19:25,664
Look at this!

380
00:19:25,747 --> 00:19:27,624
What is that? Who did that?
Why would they do that to you?

381
00:19:27,708 --> 00:19:30,252
She’s the one who always
bullies me at school.

382
00:19:30,919 --> 00:19:31,879
Huh?

383
00:19:31,962 --> 00:19:34,256
Someone bullies you at school?

384
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:35,841
At first,

385
00:19:36,508 --> 00:19:38,510
she pushed my water bottle.

386
00:19:39,595 --> 00:19:41,722
Then she teased me for being adopted.

387
00:19:42,973 --> 00:19:44,349
And now, this!

388
00:19:46,018 --> 00:19:47,186
Ah, let it go, child.

389
00:19:47,269 --> 00:19:49,646
I’ll talk to the parents
of that kid, okay?

390
00:19:54,693 --> 00:19:56,069
Come here.

391
00:20:03,660 --> 00:20:04,995
[music fades]

392
00:20:06,330 --> 00:20:07,706
- Sir.
- [scoffs]

393
00:20:07,789 --> 00:20:09,708
What really happened, Atoy?

394
00:20:09,791 --> 00:20:13,629
You don’t expect me to believe your story.

395
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:16,924
Sir, I felt bad for the child.

396
00:20:17,633 --> 00:20:22,179
Sabina needs parents who will love her.
Imagine leaving her in a boarding school.

397
00:20:22,763 --> 00:20:23,889
[sighs]

398
00:20:23,972 --> 00:20:26,975
[in English] You might have cost us
our reputation, Atoy.

399
00:20:28,101 --> 00:20:29,228
[in English] Sorry, sir.

400
00:20:30,312 --> 00:20:34,483
But at least, I know Sabina
is in good hands with Noel.

401
00:20:35,442 --> 00:20:38,195
You know, sir, what I learned from Noel?

402
00:20:38,278 --> 00:20:41,698
That being a parent is not
about name or blood…

403
00:20:43,367 --> 00:20:44,743
It’s about actions

404
00:20:45,744 --> 00:20:48,372
and keeping promises to their children.

405
00:20:49,289 --> 00:20:52,000
- [exhales]
- [mellow music playing]

406
00:20:52,084 --> 00:20:54,211
I trust your judgment.

407
00:20:55,337 --> 00:20:56,755
Sorry, sir. I’ll make it up.

408
00:20:59,007 --> 00:21:00,175
Where are you going?

409
00:21:03,595 --> 00:21:08,016
Hey, Ibyang! You even brought
a neighbor to pretend he’s your father.

410
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:09,518
What are you saying?

411
00:21:12,688 --> 00:21:14,189
I am her father.

412
00:21:21,571 --> 00:21:23,573
I just have a promise to fulfill.

413
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:31,331
[music fades]

414
00:21:31,915 --> 00:21:33,125
[Karla] You don’t want this, Ibyang?

415
00:21:33,208 --> 00:21:35,961
It’s cute! Oh, oh! Chubby! Chubby!

416
00:21:36,753 --> 00:21:38,755
It’s okay, Sis Karla.

417
00:21:40,132 --> 00:21:41,383
I know now. [clears throat]

418
00:21:41,466 --> 00:21:43,635
Ah, I know now. Ah, who has coins?

419
00:21:43,719 --> 00:21:45,304
- Do you have a peso?
- O. Peso, peso.

420
00:21:45,387 --> 00:21:47,180
- Do you have? None, none?
- What are you going to do?

421
00:21:47,264 --> 00:21:51,768
Just trust me. Don’t argue.
I’ll do magic. You don’t have coins?

422
00:21:51,852 --> 00:21:53,312
Ah! Is this what you did
when we were kids, brother?

423
00:21:53,395 --> 00:21:54,438
- Exactly this!
- Mmm!

424
00:21:54,521 --> 00:21:56,315
But this is upgraded.
Wait, you don’t have--

425
00:21:56,398 --> 00:21:57,774
- No coins, no peso?
- None.

426
00:21:57,858 --> 00:21:58,692
None?

427
00:21:58,775 --> 00:22:00,652
- Fine, here we go. Whatever.
- Brother, we don’t have money.

428
00:22:00,736 --> 00:22:02,738
Here, here, I’ll do this instead.
I’ll just invent something.

429
00:22:02,821 --> 00:22:04,156
- Watch this, Ibyang.
- Watch carefully, Ibyang.

430
00:22:04,239 --> 00:22:05,532
You’ll surely enjoy this.

431
00:22:06,616 --> 00:22:08,076
[Emerson] Mmm-hmm. Watch this.

432
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:10,829
[sneaky music playing]

433
00:22:13,915 --> 00:22:15,125
Amazing!

434
00:22:15,959 --> 00:22:17,336
Oh!

435
00:22:17,836 --> 00:22:21,131
- It becomes three, multiplying.
- [Tonet gasps]

436
00:22:21,214 --> 00:22:22,883
Oh! Right?

437
00:22:28,638 --> 00:22:30,015
She learns fast.

438
00:22:30,098 --> 00:22:31,058
You’re a good teacher.

439
00:22:31,141 --> 00:22:32,851
- But, brother, until now…
- She’s a fast learner.

440
00:22:32,934 --> 00:22:35,270
- She’s a fast learner.
- I still can’t believe how you do it.

441
00:22:35,353 --> 00:22:36,772
[Emerson] Yes, ask her.

442
00:22:36,855 --> 00:22:39,357
Your magic is so old!

443
00:22:39,441 --> 00:22:41,610
Last time I saw that
was from my grandfather.

444
00:22:41,693 --> 00:22:43,070
You still have a grandfather?

445
00:22:43,153 --> 00:22:44,654
You’re so harsh!

446
00:22:44,738 --> 00:22:47,908
Well, of course, I’m making
an effort to make the child happy.

447
00:22:47,991 --> 00:22:49,451
Oh, you, what are you doing?

448
00:22:49,534 --> 00:22:52,954
Oh. Don’t ask me what I did,
because I’ve been comforting Ibyang.

449
00:22:53,038 --> 00:22:54,748
- Hmm?
- Hey.

450
00:22:54,831 --> 00:22:57,042
Why do you two fight like…

451
00:22:57,125 --> 00:22:58,585
married couple vibes?

452
00:22:59,086 --> 00:23:01,463
[Ame] Married? With that? Yuck!

453
00:23:01,546 --> 00:23:02,464
Hmm?

454
00:23:02,547 --> 00:23:05,258
- The way you said "yuck"--
- [Emerson mutters]

455
00:23:05,342 --> 00:23:08,512
[Ame] Anyway! Let’s just tend to Ibyang.

456
00:23:08,595 --> 00:23:09,805
I know her.

457
00:23:09,888 --> 00:23:12,224
She’ll really struggle to enjoy today.

458
00:23:12,307 --> 00:23:14,351
[lively chattering]

459
00:23:14,434 --> 00:23:15,602
[Karla] Ibyang.

460
00:23:15,685 --> 00:23:16,561
[Emerson] Oh?

461
00:23:16,645 --> 00:23:18,605
- [Ame] Ibyang.
- [somber music playing]

462
00:23:20,190 --> 00:23:21,149
Ibyang.

463
00:23:21,858 --> 00:23:23,110
Psst, hey.

464
00:23:23,193 --> 00:23:25,028
Why are you sulking there?

465
00:23:25,112 --> 00:23:27,364
[indistinct chattering]

466
00:23:27,948 --> 00:23:30,867
[optimistic music playing]

467
00:23:30,951 --> 00:23:32,786
[Ibyang sobbing]

468
00:23:38,041 --> 00:23:39,042
Why?

469
00:23:39,126 --> 00:23:42,504
[sobbing]

470
00:23:43,421 --> 00:23:47,092
[sobbing]

471
00:23:47,175 --> 00:23:52,347
[electronic blipping]

472
00:23:53,431 --> 00:23:56,560
[tense music playing]

473
00:23:58,979 --> 00:24:00,939
Oh, there. We’re even now.

474
00:24:01,022 --> 00:24:02,524
- [grunts]
- [Atoy] Ibyang!

475
00:24:02,607 --> 00:24:03,441
- [Audrey] Janine!
- [clamoring]

476
00:24:03,525 --> 00:24:04,776
[Atoy] Stop that.

477
00:24:05,527 --> 00:24:06,403
[Atoy] Stop that.

478
00:24:06,987 --> 00:24:08,113
She’s your daughter?

479
00:24:09,781 --> 00:24:12,492
- How are you?
- Cathy is here too. Did you know that?

480
00:24:12,576 --> 00:24:14,035
[Gavin] <i>She has an outreach here.</i>

481
00:24:14,119 --> 00:24:15,287
<i>Will you help me with Cathy?</i>

482
00:24:15,370 --> 00:24:16,329
‪UP NEXT

483
00:24:16,413 --> 00:24:17,622
[buzzing]

484
00:24:17,706 --> 00:24:19,040
- [squeals]
- [Gavin] Hey!

485
00:24:19,124 --> 00:24:21,168
Where is…

486
00:24:21,251 --> 00:24:22,711
Ibyang’s mother?

487
00:24:22,794 --> 00:24:24,546
Can you focus first on your child?

488
00:24:25,130 --> 00:24:26,256
[in English] Sorry.

489
00:24:26,339 --> 00:24:28,425
You, where is Janine’s father?

490
00:24:28,508 --> 00:24:29,718
[dramatic stinging]

491
00:24:30,302 --> 00:24:31,511
Is she my child?

492
00:24:32,012 --> 00:24:33,221
[music swells]

493
00:24:33,305 --> 00:24:34,681
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

494
00:24:34,764 --> 00:24:36,975
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

495
00:24:37,058 --> 00:24:40,145
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i>
<i>In the tangle</i> ♪

496
00:24:40,228 --> 00:24:41,646
♪ <i>Fix this</i> ♪
